"Karjalainen T., Asikainen A.","Greenhouse gas emissions from the use of primary energy in forest operations and long-distance transportation of timber in Finland",1996,"Forestry","69","3",,"216","228",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0030436628&partnerID=40&md5=6c9f520b85b4960f30481fb5f10755ae","Faculty of Forestry, University of Joensuu, P.O. Box 111, FIN-80101 Joensuu, Finland","Karjalainen, T., Faculty of Forestry, University of Joensuu, P.O. Box 111, FIN-80101 Joensuu, Finland; Asikainen, A., Faculty of Forestry, University of Joensuu, P.O. Box 111, FIN-80101 Joensuu, Finland","In Finland in 1993 the greenhouse gas emissions caused by machinery used in silvicultural and forest improvement work, wood harvesting, and timber transportation were 424.2 Gg carbon dioxide (CO2) (Gg = gigagram = 109 g), 10.6 Mg nitrous oxide (Mg = megagram = 106 g), 3.5 Gg carbon monoxide, 31.5 Mg methane, 5.6 Gg nitrogen oxide, and 0.7 Gg non-methane volatile organic compounds. When emissions were converted into equal units as global warming potential in terms of CO2, the warming effects on a 20- year time frame equalled 1310 Gg as CO2 and on a 100-year time frame 669 Gg as CO2. The proportion of silvicultural and forest improvement work of the total emission was 8 per cent, cutting of timber 13 per cent, haulage 18 per cent, long-distance transportation 57 per cent, and transportation of machinery 4 per cent. The emissions caused by the use of primary energy in forestry seem to be small compared with the amount of carbon in harvested timber, which was 30 300 Gg in terms of CO2.",,"emission; emissions assessment; forestry; forestry operations; greenhouse gas; pollution monitoring; timber transport; timber transportation; Finland",,,,,,"(1994) Committee Report 1994:2, 145p. , (Finnish) Ministry of the Environment; Hämäläinen, J., Oijala, T., Rajamäki, J., (1992) Metsämaan Muokkauksen Kustannuslaskentamalli, 13p. , Mersäteho, Helsinki; Houghton, J.T., Jenkins, G.J., Ephraums, J.J., (1990) Climate Change, 364p. , The IPCC scientific assessment. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, UK; Houghton, J.T., Callander, B.A., Varney, S.K., (1992) Climate Change 1992, 200p. , The supplementary report to the IPCC scientific assessment, Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, UK; (1993) IPCC Draft Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories, 1-3; Karjalainen, T., Kellomaki, S., Greenhouse gas inventory for land use change and forestry in Finland based on international guidelines (1996) Mitigation and Adaptation Strategies for Global Change, 21p; Karjalainen, T., Kellomäki, S., Pussinen, A., Role of wood-based products in absorbing atmospheric carbon (1994) Silva Fenn., 28 (2), pp. 67-80; Kuitto, P.-J., Keskinen, S., Lindroos, J., Oijala, T., Rajumäki, J., Räsänen, T., Terävä, J., Mechanized cutting and forest haulage (1994) Metsateho Report, 410, p. 61; Lauhanen, R., Patu M 100-kaivuri metsaojituksessa (1992) Metsantutkimuslaitoksen Tiedonantoja, 401, 24p; (1994) Metsantutkimuslaitoksen Tiedonantoja, 516, 58p; Oijala, T., Säteri, L., (1994) Puunkorjuun ja Puutavaran Kaukokuljetuksen Tilastolukuja Vuodelta 1993, 6p. , Metsäteho, Helsinki; Energy Statistics 1993 (1994) Statistical Yearbook of Finland 1994 Energy 1994, 1, 126p; Wade, J., Holman, C., Ferguson, M., Passenger car global warming potential. Current and projected levels in the UK (1994) Energy Policy, 22 (6), pp. 509-522; Valkonen, J., Omatoimisen metsatyön kustannuslaskenta (1990) Työtehoseuran Julkaisuja, 317, 48p; (1993) Official Statistics of Finland 1994: 7, 348p. , The Finnish Forest Research Institute","Karjalainen, T.; Faculty of Forestry, University of Joensuu, P.O. Box 111, FIN-80101 Joensuu, Finland",,,,,,,,0015752X,,FRSTA,,"English","FORESTRY",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0030436628
